overview: The user's intent was to conduct a thorough test of the sleep
  questionnaire application. The approach involved systematically navigating
  through the application's UI and interacting with its features, as well as
  directly testing its API endpoints. Key decisions included using a "Pre-fill &
  Jump to Report (Dev)" button to accelerate testing of the report generation,
  and focusing on admin login error handling when credentials were not
  immediately accessible. The testing successfully verified the questionnaire
  flow, conditional field rendering, PDF report generation, and the correct
  error handling of API endpoints (e.g., for invalid admin login and incomplete
  form submissions). A notable outcome was the identification of a navigation
  bug where section transitions were not always consistent or immediately
  visible, particularly with the "Previous" and "Next Section" buttons. All API
  calls were confirmed to return expected statuses, including successful PDF and
  CSV exports, and correct error responses for authentication and validation.
